msgid "Public Keys in Monero"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:8
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! note\n"
"    Author is nowhere close to being a cryptographer. Be sceptical on accuracy.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:10
msgid ""
"Public key is deterministically derived from private key based on "
"[edwards25519 curve](/cryptography/asymmetric/edwards25519) with a little "
"Monero-specific twist."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:12
msgid ""
"Public key is meant to be shared. Assuming correct implementation, it is not "
"practically possible to recover private key from public key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:14
msgid "Public key is a **point (x,y)** on the elliptic curve."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:16
msgid "In equations points are represented by **uppercase letters**."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:19
msgid ""
"In user-facing contexts, public key is encoded in a [little-endian](https://"
"en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endianness#Little) hexadecimal form, like: "
"`016a941812293cf9a86071060fb090ab38d67945e659968cb8cf30e1bc725683`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:20
#, no-wrap
msgid "Deriving public key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:23
msgid "Say:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:27
msgid "P is a public key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:27
msgid "x is a private key"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:27
msgid ""
"G is a \"base point\"; this is simply a constant specific to [edwards25519](/"
"cryptography/asymmetric/edwards25519); this point lies on the elliptic curve"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:29
msgid "Then:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:31
#, no-wrap
msgid "    P = xG\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:34
msgid ""
"The public key is simply the base point (G) multiplied by the private key "
"(x).  Multiplying the point is adding the point to itself a number of times."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/public-key.md:39
msgid ""
"However, the addition is **not** a simple vector addition. It has a very "
"specific definition nicely described in [this article](https://blog."
"cloudflare.com/a-relatively-easy-to-understand-primer-on-elliptic-curve-"
"cryptography/).  What is important is that result of addition is always a "
"point on the curve.  For example, G + G is another point on the curve."
msgstr ""

